data.meta_description: Josephin Peladan, 1858-1918. French novelist and Martinist. Associate of Gerard Encausse (Papus), Emma Calvé, Claude Debussy and Maurice Barrès. Influenced by the writing of Eliphas Levi. He established the Mystic Order of the Rose + Croix, and the Salon de la Rose + Croix in Paris for artists, writers and musicians who shared his symbolist ideals. Founded in 1890 the Order of the Catholic Rose-Croix, the Temple and the Grail.
